<br>
I, and a small group of friends, arrived in the world of Firiona Vie about 8 months ago, and we have traveled through the lands guild-less until now.  We are reaching a point where we would like to find a home among one of FV's guild families in order to find more regular hunting partners, and travel to lands that are beyond the power of a single group of adventurers.<br>
<br>
/ooc My friends and I are looking for a guild of mature individuals to join in order to get back into casual raiding, and to find more skilled and reliable partners for experience hunting and the like.  We are all transplants from a casual raiding guild on another server.  We took a two-year break shortly after the launch of Velious, and when we returned decided to make our home on Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
We are:<br>
<br>
A 57 Paladin (me)<br>
A 55 Cleric (with a 52 Druid alternate)<br>
A 56 Enchanter<br>
A 55 Warrior<br>
<br>
We are a family, and seek to stick together in whatever guild path we follow.  We are casual role players and enjoy RP a bit, but we are likely not a good fit for a pure RP guild (and one of our band is a troll, though he has sworn off eating sentient beings, save for gnomes).  We are on Pacific time, and generally play about three hours a night (roughly 8 PM to 11 PM PST), plus a few more on weekends.  We are not looking for a power guild, we all have activities outside EQ that often pull us away from the game.  Casual raiding, casual RP, mature players, and a guild that supports its members are what we are looking for.<br>
<br>
We also have two other old companions who join us from time to time, a 49 Beastlord and 54 Monk.  I am not sure of their guild preferences at this time, but they may well look to join at a future date.<br>
<br>
If you think we might be a fit for your guild, please contact me either by posting here or sending a private message.  <br>
<br>
Thank you for your consideration.<br>
<br>
