<br>
&quot;When you described the type of Guild you were looking for, you referred to it as to Guild home. Well- that is what we are. A home. A family- loving and caring. Mature people... and elves...and all. And, above all, a band of good old friends. You said that You were a family, and seek to stick together in whatever guild path you follow- that's what we understand and appreciate most.<br>
<br>
We are not a big Guild, but we hope to grow in strength. We are not a raiding guild- but we are working on creating alliances with other Guilds that would give us the opportunity to organize serious raids. We do enjoy organizing other events- like language fairs, picnics, a storyteller contest and a beauty pageant. Most of our members are in between their 40ties and 50ties. We have both European and USA members, but they tend to visit Norrath at most awkward times of day (and night). And as for role playing- we do encourage it, however we do not force it.You should see our guildhall sometimes... <br>
<br>
